---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'bupa-global', text: 'Bupa Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'allianz-care', text: 'Allianz Care', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'teacher-needs', text: 'What Teachers Need', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Teacher Insurance Guide', href: '/insurance-for/teachers' },
  { title: 'International School Benefits', href: '/guides/international-school-benefits' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Group Plans', cigna: 'Extensive', bupa: 'Good', allianz: 'Growing' },
  { feature: 'Individual Plans', cigna: 'Yes', bupa: 'Yes', allianz: 'Yes' },
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', cigna: 'Unlimited', bupa: 'Unlimited', allianz: '€1M - €3M' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', cigna: 'Good', bupa: 'Good', allianz: 'Best' },
  { feature: 'Summer Home Coverage', cigna: 'Optional', bupa: 'Optional', allianz: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Continuation Options', cigna: 'Excellent', bupa: 'Excellent', allianz: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Maternity', cigna: 'Add-on', bupa: 'Add-on', allianz: 'Add-on' },
  { feature: 'Best For', cigna: 'International schools', bupa: 'Premium service', allianz: 'Value choice' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single Teacher, Age 30', cigna: '$250-380/mo', bupa: '$270-420/mo', allianz: '$170-250/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single Teacher, Age 40', cigna: '$350-500/mo', bupa: '$380-550/mo', allianz: '$220-330/mo' },
  { profile: 'Teacher + Spouse, Age 35', cigna: '$550-800/mo', bupa: '$600-880/mo', allianz: '$380-550/mo' },
  { profile: 'Teacher Family of 4', cigna: '$900-1,400/mo', bupa: '$1,000-1,500/mo', allianz: '$650-950/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna vs Bupa vs Allianz: Best Insurance for Teachers Abroad 2026"
  description="Compare health insurance for international teachers: Cigna Global, Bupa Global, and Allianz Care. Coverage for international school teachers, TEFL instructors, and educators abroad."
  headline="Cigna vs Bupa vs Allianz: Insurance for Teachers Abroad"
  subheadline="Whether you're at an international school or teaching ESL, here's how the three major insurers compare for educators abroad."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-2 border-primary-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Most Common</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Used by most international schools. Best for transitioning from school plans to individual. Largest network.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-purple-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Premium Service</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Premium coverage and service. Lifetime renewal. Best for long-term international educators.</p>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Value</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Comprehensive coverage at 30% less. Best mental health benefits. Great for budget-conscious teachers.</p>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    International teachers fall into two categories: those with school-provided insurance and those who need their own. Cigna dominates the international school market. If your school provides coverage, you're likely on Cigna or Bupa. For individual coverage, Allianz offers the best value.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">School Standard</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Easy Continuation</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Network</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global is the most common insurer for international schools. If your school provides insurance, there's a good chance it's Cigna. This matters because transitioning from school coverage to individual is easiest when you stay with the same insurer.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most international schools use Cigna</li>
    <li>Easy transition from group to individual</li>
    <li>Best mobile app and digital experience</li>
    <li>Largest provider network (1.5M+)</li>
    <li>Fast claims processing</li>
    <li>Unlimited coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most expensive individual rates</li>
    <li>Strict pre-existing condition handling</li>
    <li>24-month mental health waiting period</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Teachers at international schools with Cigna group coverage. Those who may switch schools but want continuity. Teachers wanting the largest network.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="bupa-global">Bupa Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Lifetime Renewal</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Premium Service</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Career Teachers</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Bupa Global is the premium choice for career international educators. Lifetime renewal means you can't be dropped, important for teachers planning decades abroad. Premium service and excellent continuation options from group plans.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Lifetime renewal guarantee</li>
    <li>Excellent continuation from group plans</li>
    <li>Premium customer service</li>
    <li>Good maternity coverage</li>
    <li>No-claims discount available</li>
    <li>Strong for long-term planning</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most expensive option</li>
    <li>App not as polished as Cigna</li>
    <li>Smaller network than Cigna</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Career international educators. Teachers who've been abroad for years. Those who value lifetime renewal and premium service.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/bupa-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="allianz-care">Allianz Care</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Value</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Mental Health</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Budget-Friendly</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Allianz Care offers the best value for teachers buying their own insurance—comprehensive coverage at 30% less than Cigna or Bupa. Mental health benefits are strongest, important for teachers dealing with the stresses of life abroad.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>30% cheaper than Cigna/Bupa</li>
    <li>Best mental health coverage</li>
    <li>Shorter mental health waiting period (12 months)</li>
    <li>Flexible on pre-existing conditions</li>
    <li>Good for ESL/TEFL teachers</li>
    <li>Monthly payment available</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>€3M coverage limit</li>
    <li>Smaller network</li>
    <li>Less common for school group plans</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> ESL/TEFL teachers buying own insurance. Budget-conscious educators. Teachers prioritizing mental health benefits.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/allianz-care" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Teacher Options"
    description="Get quotes for your teaching situation—whether school-provided or individual coverage."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    Teachers buying individual coverage see significant price differences. Allianz saves $1,200-3,600/year vs. Cigna—money that matters on teacher salaries.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated individual rates (not group). Group plan pricing depends on school contracts.
  </p>

  <h2 id="teacher-needs">What Teachers Need to Consider</h2>

  <h3>School-Provided vs. Individual</h3>
  <p>
    Two scenarios:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>International school teachers:</strong> Usually get group insurance through school (often Cigna or Bupa)</li>
    <li><strong>ESL/TEFL teachers:</strong> Usually need to buy own insurance (Allianz often best value)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Summer/Holiday Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Teachers often go home for summer. Make sure your plan covers you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>All three offer home country coverage add-ons</li>
    <li>Without it, summer visits home may not be covered</li>
    <li>Group plans may or may not include this—check yours</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Changing Schools</h3>
  <p>
    International teachers often switch schools every 2-3 years. Consider:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Staying with same insurer when possible</li>
    <li>Continuation options when leaving a school</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions developed at one school carry to next</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Mental Health</h3>
  <p>
    Teaching abroad is rewarding but challenging. Mental health coverage matters:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Best—50 sessions/year, 12-month wait</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Good—30-40 sessions/year, 12-month wait</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Good—20-30 sessions/year, 24-month wait</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Families and Maternity</h3>
  <p>
    Many teachers start families abroad:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>All three offer maternity add-ons (10-12 month waiting period)</li>
    <li>Bupa has highest maternity limits</li>
    <li>Check if school plan includes maternity</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Have Cigna through your current school</li>
        <li>Plan to switch international schools</li>
        <li>Want the largest provider network</li>
        <li>Value the best digital experience</li>
        <li>Can afford premium pricing</li>
        <li>Want easy school-to-individual transition</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Bupa Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are a career international educator</li>
        <li>Want lifetime renewal guarantee</li>
        <li>Plan to teach abroad for many years</li>
        <li>Have Bupa through your current school</li>
        <li>Value premium customer service</li>
        <li>Want no-claims discounts</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Allianz Care if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are an ESL/TEFL teacher buying own insurance</li>
        <li>Are budget-conscious</li>
        <li>Prioritize mental health coverage</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Want good coverage at fair prices</li>
        <li>Don't have school-provided insurance</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Should I keep my school's insurance or get my own?</h3>
  <p>
    Usually keep the school's plan—it's free and covers you. But consider supplementing with your own if: (1) school plan has gaps, (2) you have conditions that developed while teaching that you want protected when you leave, or (3) you want portability.
  </p>

  <h3>What happens to my insurance when I change schools?</h3>
  <p>
    School coverage ends when employment ends. If your new school uses the same insurer, transition is easy. If different, you may need to apply fresh—and any conditions developed become pre-existing for the new insurer.
  </p>

  <h3>Is insurance included in most teaching contracts?</h3>
  <p>
    International schools (IB curriculum, etc.) typically include insurance. ESL/TEFL positions often don't—or provide minimal local coverage. Check your contract carefully.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I continue my school plan when I leave?</h3>
  <p>
    Usually yes, through a "continuation" option. You pay the full premium yourself. Contact your insurer 60-90 days before leaving to arrange this. Cigna and Bupa have the smoothest continuation processes.
  </p>

  <h3>What about coverage during job searches between schools?</h3>
  <p>
    Don't let coverage lapse. Either continue your old school's plan or get individual coverage. Gaps reset pre-existing condition timelines and can leave you exposed during job transitions.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> School-provided insurance varies by contract. This comparison covers general patterns and individual plan options. Check your specific school contract for your actual coverage details.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
